   "source": [
    "# Critical Buckling Verification Study\n",
    "\n",
    "Presented within Rafael's master dissertation \"COMPOSITE PLATE OPTIMIZATION COMBINING SEMIANALYTICAL MODEL, LAMINATION PARAMETERS AND A GRADIENT-BASED OPTIMIZER\". \n",
    "\n",
    "Access the full repository with complete study and NASTRAN FEM model at: https://github.com/rafaelpsilva07/rafaelmscdissertation\n",
    "\n",
    "The following examples are part of the Ritz verification against FEM model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Simply Supported study case (SSSS)\n",
    "\n",
    "This study case aims to verify the Rayleigh-Ritz implementation made with Composipy (Silva,\n",
    "R.P. 2023). Mathematical verification of the Rayleigh-Ritz implementation is made against\n",
    "analytical buckling equation and FEM model.\n",
    "The benchmarking example is a simply supported plate with biaxial load, which considers a\n",
    "quasi-isotropic layup [(45/-45)2/02/902]s and properties according Table below. This example came\n",
    "from Kassapoglou (2010).\n",
    "\n",
    "<img src=\"./mechanical_prop_verification_problem.png\" width=\"400\" height=\"200\">\n",
    "\n",
    "Dimension of the square plate is 100 mm and the load ratio (ùëÅùë¶/ùëÅùë•) is 0.5. Analytical solution\n",
    "for this problem using Equation below is 234.7 N/mm.\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\lambda = \\pi^2\\frac{[D_{11}m^4 +2(D_{12}+2D_{66})m^2n^2(a/b)^2 + D_{22}n^4(a/b)^4  ]}{a^2 (m^2 + (N_{x}/N_{y}) n^2 (a/b)^2)}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "This problem using composipy results in 225.9 N/mm. See code below."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from composipy import OrthotropicMaterial, LaminateProperty, PlateStructure"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "min eigenvalue is  225.9 N/mm\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "E1 = 137.9e3\n",
    "E2 = 11.7e3\n",
    "v12 = 0.31\n",
    "G12 = 4.82e3\n",
    "t = 0.1524\n",
    "\n",
    "a = 100\n",
    "b = 100\n",
    "\n",
    "Nxx = -1\n",
    "Nyy = -0.5\n",
    "\n",
    "m = 7\n",
    "n = 7\n",
    "\n",
    "mat = OrthotropicMaterial(E1, E2, v12, G12, t)\n",
    "stack = [45, -45]*2 + [0]*2 + [90]*2\n",
    "stack += stack[::-1]\n",
    "lam = LaminateProperty(stack, mat)\n",
    "plate = PlateStructure(lam, a, b, \"PINNED\", Nxx=Nxx, Nyy=Nyy, m=m, n=n)\n",
    "\n",
    "eigenvalue, eigenvector = plate.buckling_analysis()\n",
    "print(f'min eigenvalue is {eigenvalue[0]: .1f} N/mm')\n",
    "\n",
    "plate.plot_eigenvalue()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Different boundary conditions\n",
    "Table below extends the study for different boundary conditions in order to verify polynomial\n",
    "functions presented in section 2.1.3. The results are verified against a NASTRAN FEM model\n",
    "and the maximum difference is 0.7%. Table 6 presents the first buckling mode deformation\n",
    "shape.\n",
    "\n",
    "<img src=\"./first_eigenvalue_BC.png\"  height=\"150\">\n",
    "\n",
    "### Clamped study case (CCCC)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "min eigenvalue is  495.0 N/mm\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "lam = LaminateProperty(stack, mat)\n",
    "plate = PlateStructure(lam, a, b, \"CLAMPED\", Nxx=Nxx, Nyy=Nyy, m=m, n=n)\n",
    "\n",
    "eigenvalue, eigenvector = plate.buckling_analysis()\n",
    "print(f'min eigenvalue is {eigenvalue[0]: .1f} N/mm')\n",
    "\n",
    "plate.plot_eigenvalue()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
